'''G-8Y5''' was an engineering [[Droid/Legends|droid]] on [[Uffel]]. [[QS-2D]] considered G-8Y5 its greatest creation, better than its model of [[Battle droid/Legends|war droids]] or the single droid that controlled (or "was") the entire [[Spaceport/Legends|spaceport]] of [[X2-4]] [[City/Legends|City]].

G-8Y5's role was to upgrade Uffel's droids and keep them in working condition, and also to develop new droid types. G-8Y5 developed Uffel's space weapon platforms, who saw first use when defeating a [[Pirate/Legends|pirate]] attack in [[33 BBY/Legends|33 BBY]]. It could have played a large role in developing the [[MSF mouse droid|MSF-series]] mouse droids and Uffel's advanced [[Battle droid/Legends|war droid]] defenders. G-8Y5 developed many prototype droids, some of which were sold to buyers elsewhere in the [[Cularin system/Legends|Cularin system]]. Many owners of strange droids claimed that they were from Uffel, but that was not always true.

G-8Y5 worked along with [[4-KT]] in droid design.

